---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Product Managers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Product Managers working internationally, covering product leadership positions abroad, technology product careers, and global product management opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Product Managers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Product Managers working abroad, building products internationally, and pursuing careers across technology, SaaS, and digital product companies worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/product-manager-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/product-manager-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Product Manager Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Product Managers define product vision, prioritize features, and guide development teams to build products customers want. International product management offers opportunities to build products for global markets, work with distributed teams, and shape products used across countries.
      </p>
      <p>
        International product management opportunities exist through technology companies, SaaS providers, digital platforms, and organizations building products for international markets.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Product Managers working abroad across technology, SaaS, and digital product companies worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Product Managers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Decision pressure and stakeholder management', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Eye coverage', why: 'Screen-intensive analysis and documentation', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Office-based work', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Customer research and team visits', typical: 'Often needed' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'High-pressure decision environment', typical: 'Often included' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Decision Accountability</h3>
      <p>
        Product managers make decisions that significantly impact business outcomes—what to build, what not to build, and how to prioritize. Every launch, every feature decision, every roadmap call is visible. The stress of product accountability creates substantial mental health demands. Mental health support helps manage decision pressure.
      </p>
      <p>
        PMs also navigate competing stakeholder interests—engineering, design, sales, marketing, and executives all have opinions about product direction.
      </p>

      <h3>Screen-Intensive Work</h3>
      <p>
        Product managers spend extensive time with screens—analyzing data, writing PRDs, reviewing designs, managing backlogs, and communicating via various tools. Eye and ergonomic coverage supports the digital-intensive nature of product work.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>SaaS/Technology</h3>
      <p>
        Software product management. Premium tech benefits. Feature velocity. Tech offers compensation and equity.
      </p>

      <h3>E-commerce</h3>
      <p>
        Platform or marketplace products. E-commerce benefits. Conversion focus. E-commerce offers scale.
      </p>

      <h3>Fintech</h3>
      <p>
        Financial product management. Fintech benefits. Compliance integration. Fintech offers compensation.
      </p>

      <h3>Consumer Products</h3>
      <p>
        Consumer apps or platforms. Consumer tech benefits. User growth focus. Consumer offers impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p>
        B2B product management. Enterprise benefits. Customer-driven development. Enterprise offers stability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Product Managers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across technology, SaaS, and digital product companies worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Product Manager Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Product Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Shipped products. Growth metrics. Revenue impact. Track record primary credential.
      </p>

      <h3>Domain Expertise</h3>
      <p>
        Industry knowledge. Market understanding. Technical fluency. Domain expertise valued highly.
      </p>

      <h3>Product Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        Product School, Pragmatic Institute credentials. Methodology training. Certifications demonstrate commitment.
      </p>

      <h3>Technical Background</h3>
      <p>
        Engineering or technical degree. Development understanding. Technical PMs valued. Background helpful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Decision Stress</h3>
      <p>
        Roadmap accountability. Feature prioritization. Launch pressure. Mental health support critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Screen Time</h3>
      <p>
        Data analysis. Documentation. Tool management. Eye coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Stakeholder Management</h3>
      <p>
        Competing interests. Difficult conversations. Influence without authority. Stress management valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Cognitive Load</h3>
      <p>
        Context switching. Information synthesis. Constant prioritization. Wellness support helpful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Discovery</h3>
      <p>
        Customer research. Market analysis. Problem identification. Discovery ensures product-market fit.
      </p>

      <h3>Definition</h3>
      <p>
        Requirements writing. PRD creation. Specification detail. Definition guides development.
      </p>

      <h3>Prioritization</h3>
      <p>
        Backlog management. Roadmap decisions. Trade-off navigation. Prioritization allocates resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Launch</h3>
      <p>
        Go-to-market coordination. Release management. Success measurement. Launch delivers value.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Strong Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Tech growth driving PM demand. Product-led organizations growing. International opportunities expanding. Demand excellent.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior PM. Group PM. Director of Product. VP Product. CPO. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Product skills transfer. Domain knowledge may be specific. Track record portable. Experience valued globally.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        AI products. Product-led growth. Remote product work. Field evolving rapidly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a product manager considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech companies provide strong benefits. Remote PM roles growing. Product skills transfer well. Market knowledge may need building.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Technology companies yes. Startups vary. Enterprise companies comprehensive. Benefits typically strong in tech.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is decision pressure a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes in PM roles. Roadmap accountability high. Stakeholder pressure constant. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do product management skills transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Core skills transfer well. Market specifics vary. Customer research adapts. Product methodology universal.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is travel common for PMs?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Less than some roles. Customer research visits helpful. Team coordination may require travel. Remote work common.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Product roles growing. Tech expansion continues. Product thinking valued broadly. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Consider mental health support for decision pressure. Include eye coverage for screen-intensive work. Verify international coverage scope for your product organization.
      </p>
      <p>
        Product Managers shape products globally. Your coverage should support PM careers—addressing decision and screen-work demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across product work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Product Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Product Managers working abroad across technology, SaaS, and digital product companies worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
